{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":328000,"duration_api_ms":302065,"num_turns":46,"result":"Now I have the schema format. Let me produce the JSON response:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Fixed three issues: (1) first retry no longer waits 5s unnecessarily — backoff now uses cursor.attempt-1 so attempt 1 gets zero delay, (2) map_invoke_error now preserves BackendUnavailable errors (including terminal BinaryNotFound classification) instead of converting them to InvocationFailed{TransportFailure}, (3) OpenRouter invoke path rejects blank OPENROUTER_API_KEY with terminal BinaryNotFound classification matching check_availability behavior.\",\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Changed engine.rs backoff call from backoff_for_attempt(cursor.attempt) to backoff_for_attempt(cursor.attempt - 1) so first retry (attempt=1) produces backoff_for_attempt(0)=ZERO, and backoff ramps on repeated failures\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added BackendUnavailable match arm to map_invoke_error in service.rs so invoke-time BackendUnavailable errors (e.g. missing API key with failure_class: Some(BinaryNotFound)) pass through unchanged instead of being wrapped as InvocationFailed{TransportFailure}\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Changed process_backend.rs OpenRouter command builder to check for both missing and empty OPENROUTER_API_KEY using .ok().filter(|k| !k.is_empty()), returning InvocationFailed with FailureClass::BinaryNotFound (terminal) consistent with check_availability and openrouter_backend.rs\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Renamed test invoke_openrouter_without_api_key_returns_transport_failure to invoke_openrouter_without_api_key_returns_terminal_failure, updated assertion to verify FailureClass::BinaryNotFound\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added new test invoke_openrouter_with_blank_api_key_returns_terminal_failure verifying empty string OPENROUTER_API_KEY also returns terminal BinaryNotFound\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Verified all 679 tests pass, cargo clippy clean, cargo fmt --check clean\",\n      \"order\": 6,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 679 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored\",\n    \"cargo clippy: no warnings or errors\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: no formatting differences\",\n    \"Test invoke_openrouter_without_api_key_returns_terminal_failure verifies missing key returns BinaryNotFound\",\n    \"Test invoke_openrouter_with_blank_api_key_returns_terminal_failure verifies empty key returns BinaryNotFound\",\n    \"Existing backoff_for_attempt(0) test from CR9 confirms ZERO is returned for the first-retry case\"\n  ],\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"BackendUnavailable errors passing through map_invoke_error will now surface with their original error variant to the engine retry loop; the engine's failure_class() extraction already handles BackendUnavailable correctly, but any consumer matching only on InvocationFailed may need updating\",\n    \"The cursor.attempt - 1 subtraction is safe because StageCursor::new rejects attempt=0, so cursor.attempt is always >= 1 at this point\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":2.5307107500000012,"usage":{"input_tokens":41,"cache_creation_input_tokens":47496,"cache_read_input_tokens":1719621,"output_tokens":8941,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":47496,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTo